It Is Time to Remember: Why Do You Do What You Do?

December 5, 2025

Wow… another year has come and gone.
Is it just me, or is time moving faster than ever?

Maybe time is not speeding up at all but maybe we are.
Maybe the collective is becoming more awake, more aware, more aligned with what reality truly is.

And with this shift, one question keeps rising to the surface:

Why do you do what you do?

Before you answer, pause. Feel the weight of that question.
Let’s go deeper.

Why do you wake up every morning and drag yourself into a job that may not inspire you?
Why do you pour so much effort into people who do not reciprocate the same love or energy?
Why do you continue numbing your pain with addictions, distractions, and loops that keep you stuck?

Why?
Because underneath all these “whys” is a much bigger question:

Do you truly know who you are… and why you are here?

Most people will never ask themselves this.
Some are too afraid of the answer.
Others are too lost in the noise of the world to even hear the question.

But let’s be honest:
Do you really believe we were once apes and somehow “evolved” into human beings with consciousness, imagination, creativity, emotion, spirit, intuition, and the capacity to reshape reality itself?

Come on.
Everything created has purpose.
Everything created has intention.

And that includes you.

You Are a Soul Given One Body, One Lifetime, One Opportunity

We are spiritual beings having a human experience not the other way around.
Your soul incarnated into your body the moment you took your first breath.
One body.
One vessel.
One chance to experience a dense, physical world full of duality, contrast, and lessons.

Earth is not just a planet.
Earth is a school.
A training ground.
A place where your soul learns through experience, love, loss, struggle, joy, and creation.

But along the way, something happens…

We live the “normal life” we were taught to follow without question.
We absorb beliefs that are not ours.
We store pain, fear, and trauma within our bodies.
We disconnect from our spirit.
We forget who we are.

And the result?
Disease.
Disconnection.
Numbness.
Confusion.
A life lived on autopilot instead of intention.

But here’s the truth:
You did not come here to live a life full of suffering.
You came here to create.
You came here to express.
You came here to experience your highest potential.

And you ca not do that while carrying the weight of everything that broke you.

Creation Requires Clearing. Letting Go of the Burdens You Were Never Meant to Carry

To create a life aligned with your essence, you must release what no longer belongs in your body or your mind.
You must become honest with yourself.
You must communicate your truth.
And you must be willing to look at the pain you’ve been avoiding for years.

Because here is the thing:
Most people do not live their own lives.
They live the life someone else told them to.

Parents
Teachers
Governments
Religions
Society

People follow “the rules” without ever questioning the authority behind them.
They trade their power for approval.
They trade their sovereignty for comfort.
They trade their authenticity for acceptance.

But here is a truth many are not ready for:

No man has power or authority over another man.

Only over a person.
And a person is just a character or a mask you wear in the system.
A mask you were conditioned to assume.

This is why people feel lost.
Because they are living as a “person”… not as a soul.

Most People Are not Living. They are Running

Running from the inner work.
Running from their pain.
Running toward distractions that temporarily silence what is screaming inside.

The world convinces us that money, status, entertainment, and appearances matter more than inner alignment.
But none of those things can fix the emptiness that comes from ignoring your true self.

The only things that truly matter are:

You.
Your body.
Your mind.
Your spirit.
Your internal and external environment.

Everything else is background noise.

Free Will Has a Limit. Alignment Does Not

What many do not realize is that free will is sacred but delicate.
Most of what people choose to do every day is not aligned with divine law, divine truth, or divine intention.
They live from ego, fear, trauma, or programming not from spirit.

True alignment begins when you understand this reality:

Everything starts spiritual.
Then it becomes mental.
Then it becomes physical.

This is the human experience.
Spirit → Mind → Matter.

If your spirit is disconnected, your mind becomes confused.
If your mind is confused, your body follows.
Your life becomes a reflection of your misalignment.

It is Time to Ask Yourself the Real Questions

Do I know who I am?
Do I know who God is?
Do I understand why my soul chose this lifetime?
Do I know my purpose?
Am I living, or am I performing?
Am I creating, or am I consuming?
Am I awake, or am I still asleep?

These questions are not meant to scare you.
They are meant to awaken you.

To explore them, you must realign the trinity within you:

Mind
Body
Spirit

This is how you reclaim sovereignty.
This is how you step into your purpose.
This is how you remember who you are.

You came here for a reason.
You were born into this time for a reason.
You are waking up for a reason.

It is time to remember.
And the remembering begins now


man hunter johnson
